---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Section from '../components/Section.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Research"
  description="Research themes across medical image computing, clinical AI evaluation, workflow-oriented healthcare AI, and generative/agentic AI."
>
  <Section title="Research Themes">
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        This page summarizes research themes at the boundary of medical image computing, clinical
        AI productization, and healthcare workflow systems.
      </p>
      <p>
        The themes are written for both academic and industry audiences, with links to selected
        outputs across publications and projects.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="list section">
      <article class="item">
        <h3>1. Medical Image Retrieval and Representation Learning</h3>
        <p>
          Focused on scalable retrieval and representation learning for clinical and biomedical
          image collections, including metric- and hashing-based approaches.
        </p>
        <p class="meta">
          Representative methods and systems include Metric Hashing Forests, Deep Multiple
          Instance Hashing, and Neuron-Miner.
        </p>
        <p>
          <a href="/publications">See related publications</a>
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="item">
        <h3>2. Segmentation, Uncertainty, and Neuroimaging Pipelines</h3>
        <p>
          Combines efficient segmentation with structure-wise quality control and uncertainty
          estimation for neuroimaging workflows.
        </p>
        <p class="meta">
          Representative systems include QuickNAT, Bayesian QuickNAT, and FastSurfer.
        </p>
        <p>
          <a href="/publications">See related publications</a>
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="item">
        <h3>3. Multimodal Imaging and Computational Pathology</h3>
        <p>
          Addresses multimodal learning and cross-modal analysis across OCT, MRI, pathology, and
          related domains, including registration and whole-slide analysis.
        </p>
        <p class="meta">
          Representative contributions include ReLayNet and multimodal registration methods used in
          pathology and image alignment workflows.
        </p>
        <p>
          <a href="/publications">See related publications</a>
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="item">
        <h3>4. Clinical AI Evaluation and Reporting Support</h3>
        <p>
          Focuses on evaluation frameworks, clinically meaningful validation, and AI-assisted
          reporting support in radiology and endoscopy-adjacent contexts.
        </p>
        <p class="meta">
          Publicly documented examples include multicenter chest X-ray AI evaluation work and
          reporting-support invention themes.
        </p>
        <p>
          <a href="/publications">Publications</a> · <a href="/patents">Patents</a>
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="item">
        <h3>5. Workflow-Oriented Healthcare AI</h3>
        <p>
          Centers on integrating AI into day-to-day clinical operations, including reporting,
          documentation, interoperability, and workflow orchestration.
        </p>
        <p class="meta">
          Representative systems-level direction includes endoscopy workflow management and
          AI-enabled clinical workflow support.
        </p>
        <p>
          <a href="/projects">Projects</a> · <a href="/products">Products</a>
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="item">
        <h3>6. Generative and Agentic AI in Healthcare</h3>
        <p>
          Explores practical use of generative and agentic AI for healthcare prototyping,
          education, and workflow support, with emphasis on reliability and evaluation.
        </p>
        <p class="meta">
          This includes retrieval-augmented patterns, agentic workflows, and implementation-focused
          teaching and mentoring.
        </p>
        <p>
          <a href="/teaching">Teaching</a> · <a href="/projects">Projects</a> · <a href="/writing">Writing</a>
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </Section>
</BaseLayout>
